{
  "stem": "521.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the rest of them were gathering in the middle of the camp and very nicely attired were sitting there and were waiting for the Americans to come.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Americans came, and they're gone.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we started to eat very solid meat, conserved, how do you-- canned meat.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they started to die because of diarrhea, which was a result of eating that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, after this the Americans have kept us and put us on trucks.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "About two days later, we were transported into a barrack, which was used by the Germans for the soldiers.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were put there in beds, and most of us had diarrhea.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But before, I have to commemorate a very, very good hearted, reasonable person whose name I don't know.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I saw him giving bread to people who couldn't move anymore.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was after the liberation.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Another Jew had a loaf of bread and cut small pieces of bread and was feeding it to other Jews who couldn't move anymore.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Now I will never, ever forget it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "How much sacrifice he made because it wasn't his business to keep somebody else alive, and he was trying his level best.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I was too young to understand at that time and to imitate it, but it was something special, which is really remarkable.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then, we were given over to the Germans in that barracks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the Germans were supposed to look after us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Americans said to the Germans, see German, these are Jews you wanted to kill, now you have to feed them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I have seen that the Germans were putting water into the milk and it became blue because it was so little milk in it.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
